# AGENTS.md instructions

To work in this local environment, first call `uv run prompt_forge agent_help`
and follow its loading rules.

## Domain primitives

Do not use raw `str`, `int`, or `uuid.UUID` for domain/business-owned values.
Use the project primitives from `app/schemas/typings/` instead.

- IDs must use primitives from `app/schemas/typings/ids.py`.
- Domain strings must use primitives from `app/schemas/typings/strings.py`.
- Domain integers must use primitives from `app/schemas/typings/integers.py`.
- If the required primitive does not exist yet, add a clearly named primitive to
  the owning `app/schemas/typings/` module before using it in DTOs, documents,
  contracts, use cases, or other business code.
- Raw `str`, `int`, and `uuid.UUID` are allowed only at external boundaries
  before validation/parsing, or for purely technical values that are not domain
  data.

After boundary validation, business code must receive typed primitives, not raw
Python primitives.
